# VPN_SWITCH_PSEUDO_PROTOCOL - Space-separated list of pseudo-protocol directories
#
# Pseudo-protocols are top-level directories in VPN_SWITCH_BASE that are NOT
# VPN protocols (like wireguard, openvpn). They are used for special purposes:
#
#   session      - Named session symlinks (work → ../.session/12345)
#   environment  - Environment variable overrides
#
# Hidden directories (.session, .build, .log, .include, .env) are handled
# separately by the .* pattern in is_pseudo_protocol().
#
# Used by:
#   - __start0: Protocol discovery (skip pseudo-protocols when selecting VPN)
#   - ___stop0: Protocol enumeration (skip pseudo-protocols when stopping)
#
# Default value: "session environment"
#
# Testing override:
#   To test "no protocols found" error paths, add real protocols to this list:
#   VPN_SWITCH_PSEUDO_PROTOCOL="session environment wireguard openvpn"
